cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for testing list homomorphisms, which are related to graph coloring and constraint satisfaction problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves complexity analysis and algorithm design, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of graph structures and properties makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper involves some game-theoretic concepts, which could place it in cs.GT (Game Theory).
